1  West Bromwich Commercial Limited - Limited Company Buy to Let Mortgage Conditions 2018  (The “General Conditions”)  1.   Definitions and Interpretation  1.1   In each Facility Document.  “AST”   means an assured shorthold tenancy governed by the Housing Act 1988 (as amended).  “Authorisation”   means an authorisation, consent, approval, resolution, licence, exemption, filing, notarisation or registration.  “Borrower”   means the person named in the Facility Letter as ‘the Borrower’.  “Business Day”   means any weekday on which banks are generally open for business in London.  “Charged Property”   means the freehold or leasehold property (or other interest in land or buildings)  specified in the Facility Letter as the   “Property” , and any other freehold or leasehold property over which the Borrower or any Security Provider has granted Security in favour of the Lender, and includes any part of that property.  “Deed of Priority”   means any document that is expressed to regulate the priority of a Security Document and is executed in favour of the Lender.  “Default Interest”   means a rate of interest 2% per annum above the Interest Rate from time to time.  “EPC”   means an Energy Performance Certificate produced pursuant to the Energy Performance of Buildings  (England and Wales) Regulations 2012 (SI 2012/3118) and the Building Regulations 2010 (SI 2010/2214) (as amended).  “Environment”   means humans, animals, plants and all other living organisms including the ecological systems of which they form part and the following media:  a)   air (including, without limitation, air within natural or man-made structures, whether above or below ground) b)   water (including, without limitation, territorial, coastal and inland waters, water under or within land and water in drains and sewers) and c)   land (including, without limitation, land under water)  “Environmental Law”   means any applicable law or regulation which relates to:  a)   the pollution or protection of the Environment b)   energy efficiency at a property, including MEES or c)   the generation, handling, storage, use, release or spillage of any substance which, alone or in  combination with any other, is capable of causing harm to the Environment, including, without limitation, any waste  “Event of Default”   means any of the events set out in General Condition 13 or any additional event of default specifically listed in the Facility Letter.  “Facility Documents”   means the Facility Letter, each Security Document, any Guarantee, any Professional Warranty, any Deed of Priority, these General Conditions and any other document that the Lender and the Borrower agree is a Facility Document and   “Facility Document”   means any one of them.  “Facility Letter”   means any letter of offer, facility letter or offer to make further loans to the Borrower in which the Lender agrees to provide loan facilities or other financial accommodation to the Borrower (as  amended, supplemented or varied from time to time).  “Guarantee”   means any guarantee given by a Guarantor.  “Guarantor”   means any person that guarantees any obligation of the Borrower or a Security Provider to the Lender.
2  “Increased Cost”   means.  a)   any additional or increased cost incurred by the Lender or any affiliate of the Lender as a result of it  having entered into or performing, maintaining or funding its obligations under the Facility Documents, or  b)   a reduction of any amount due and payable under the Facility Documents or a reduction in the rate of return from the Loan or on the Lender’s (or an affiliate of the Lender’s) overall capital incurred by the  Lender or any affiliate of the Lender as a result of it having entered into or performing, maintaining or funding its obligations under the Facility Documents, in each case arising out of any change in or introduction of (or the interpretation, administration or  application of) any law or regulation or compliance with any law or regulation made after the date of the  Facility Letter.  “Insurance Policy”   means each contract or policy of insurance relating to a Charged Property in which the Borrower or a Security Provider has an interest.  “Insured Risks”   means fire, explosion, collision, impact, storm, flood, lightning, landslip, subsidence, burst  pipes, malicious damage, acts of terrorism, six months’ loss of rent, third party and public liability and such  other risks as the Lender may from time to time reasonably require.  “Interest”   means any amount payable to the Lender by way of interest on the Loan or the Loan Obligations or any part thereof.  “Interest Rate”   means the rate(s) of interest (as varied from time to time) payable on the Loan (or on different parts of the Loan) in accordance with the Facility Letter.  “Legal Charge”   means each mortgage or legal charge in respect of all or any part of a Charged Property executed by the Borrower or any Security Provider as security for the Loan and the Loan Obligations.  “Lease”   means any lease, underlease, sub-lease, licence, tenancy (including an AST) or right to occupy all  or any part of a Charged Property or right to receive rent to which a Charged Property may at any time be  subject and includes any guarantee of a tenant’s obligations under the same and any agreement for the grant  of a Lease.  “Lender”   means the person identified in the Facility Letter as ‘the Lender’ (and any successor in title to such person) or any person entitled to the rights of the Lender under the Facility Letter pursuant to any assignment  or transfer of the Loan.  “Limited Company Buy to Let Variable Rate”   means the Buy to Let Variable lending rate of the Lender from  time to time, being such annual percentage rate as is published by the Lender from time to time and/or as  notified to the Borrower by the Lender from time to time.  “Loan”   means a loan made or to be made by the Lender to the Borrower pursuant to the terms of the Facility Letter or the principal amount outstanding for the time being of that loan.  “Loan Obligations”   means all present and future obligations and liabilities (whether actual or contingent, whether owed jointly, severally or in any other capacity whatsoever and on whatever account and whether  originally incurred by the Borrower, the Security Provider or by some other person) of the Borrower and/  or any Security Provider to the Lender, and all costs, charges and expenses incurred by the Lender in  connection with the preservation, protection or enforcement of the Lender’s rights under, and/or the Security  constituted by, the Facility Documents.  Material Adverse Effect   means, in the reasonable opinion of the Lender, a material adverse effect on:  a)   the property or financial condition of the Borrower or any Security Provider or b)   the ability of the Borrower or any Security Provider to perform its obligations under the Facility  Documents or  c)   the validity or enforceability of, or the effectiveness or ranking of any Security or guarantee granted or  purported to be granted pursuant to any of, the Facility Documents or  d)   the rights or remedies of the Lender under any of the Facility Documents “ MEES”   means minimum energy efficiency standards pursuant to the Energy Efficiency (Private Rental  Property) (England and Wales) Regulations 2015 (SI2015/962).
3  “Professional Warranties”   means each deed of collateral warranty granted in favour of the Lender by (but  not limited to) any architect, building contractor, engineer, quantity surveyor, construction manager or other  person employed by the Borrower, a Security Provider or a third party in respect of a Charged Property.  “Receiver”   means a receiver (including a receiver appointed under the Law of Property Act 1925) or receiver  and manager of the whole or any part of the Security Assets.  “Repayment Date”   means the date specified in the Facility Letter as the date by which the Loan and all other Loan Obligations must be repaid to the Lender in full (or, if that date is not a Business Day, the  immediately preceding Business Day).  “Security”   means a mortgage, charge, security assignment, guarantee, professional warranty, pledge, lien or other security interest securing any obligation of any person or any other agreement or arrangement having a similar effect.  “Security Asset”   means all of the assets of the Borrower or any Security Provider which from time to time are, or are expressed to be, the subject of the Transaction Security.  “Security Document”   means each Legal Charge and any other document creating or purporting to create  Security over any assets of the Borrower or any Security Provider as security for the Loan and/or other Loan  Obligations or any other document designated as such by the Lender and the Borrower.  “Security Provider”   means any person who grants or is to grant Security to the Lender to secure the Loan  and/or the Loan Obligations. “ Tariff of Charges ” means the tariff of charges issued by the Lender from time to time or may be requested  from the Lender.  “Transaction Security”   means the Security created or evidenced or expressed to be created or evidenced under the Security Documents.  “VAT”   means any tax imposed in compliance with the Value Added Tax Act 1994 and any other tax of a similar nature in substitution for, or levied in addition to, such tax. 1.2   Unless a contrary indication appears, any reference in the Facility Documents to  (i)   “control”   or   “gains control”   means  (a)   the power to (i)   cast, or control the casting of, more than 30% of the maximum number or votes that might be  cast at a general meeting of the relevant entity, or  (ii)   appoint or remove all, or the majority, of the directors or other equivalent officers of the  relevant entity, or  (iii)   give directions with respect to the operating and financial policies of the relevant entity with  which the director or other equivalent officers of the relevant entity are obliged to comply, or  (b)   the holding of more than 30% of the issued share capital of the relevant entity (but excluding any  part of that issued share capital that carries no right to participate beyond a specified amount in a  distribution of either profits or capital) (ii)   “ person ” includes any person, firm, company, corporation, government, state or agency of a state,  association, unincorporated body of persons, trust or partnership (whether or not having a separate legal  personality) and any two or more of the foregoing (iii)   “subsidiary” means in relation to any company or corporation, a company or corporation (a)   which is controlled, directly or indirectly, by the first mentioned company or corporation (b)   more than half the issued share capital of which is beneficially owned, directly or indirectly by the  first mentioned company or corporation, or  (c)   which is a subsidiary or another subsidiary of the first mentioned company or corporation and for  this purpose, a company or corporation shall be treated as being controlled by another if that other  company or corporation is able to direct its affairs and/or to control the composition of its boards of  directors or equivalent body
4  (iv)   the law or any statute means all Acts of Parliament, Statutory Instruments and all subordinate legislation  deriving out of statutes or statutory instruments and all legislation of a regional or local nature including European Community legislation and directives  (v)   “us”, “we” and “our” and any related expression are references to the Lender and “you” or “your” and any related expressions are references to the Borrower and/or a Security Provider and (vi)   the “ Lender ”, the “ Borrower ”, any “ Security   Provider ” or any other person shall be construed so as to include its successors in title, permitted assigns and permitted transferees to, or of, its rights and/or  obligations under the Facility Documents 1.3   The headings in these General Conditions are for ease of reference only and shall not affect construction. 1.4   Any reference in a Facility Document to a provision of law is to that provision as amended or re-enacted. 1.5   Any reference in a Facility Document to a Facility Document or any other agreement or instrument is a reference to that Facility Document or other agreement or instrument as amended, novated, supplemented,  extended, replaced or restated (however fundamentally).  1.6   The General Conditions are incorporated into each applicable Facility Document as if set out in each such Facility Document in full.  1.7   An Event of Default is “ continuing ” if it has not been waived by the Lender in writing.  1.8   If there is any conflict or inconsistency between the terms of the General Conditions and the terms of the Facility Letter, the terms of the Facility Letter shall prevail.  2.   Interest  2.1   the date of advance of the funds for the Loan up to (and including) the date on which the Loan is repaid  in full. 2.2   The Borrower will pay accrued interest on the Loan on the last day of each calendar month, commencing on the last day of the calendar month in which the Loan is made. 2.3   If any sum payable by the Borrower or a Security Provider under the Facility Documents (including any  charges, costs or expenses (including legal costs)) incurred pursuant to these General Conditions is not paid  on or by its due date (or any judgment of any court in connection with any Facility Document is not paid  within the period required under such judgement) Default Interest will accrue on that overdue amount from the due date up to the date of actual payment (both before and after judgment) and all Default Interest is  payable by the Borrower or the relevant Security Provider on demand by the Lender.  3.   Changing the Interest Rate  3.1   Except during any period when interest is stated in the Facility Letter to be charged at a fixed rate, the Lender has the power to vary the Interest Rate in accordance with this General Condition 3. 3.2   The Lender has the right to review its Limited Company Buy to Let Variable Rate at any time. 3.3   The Lender may increase its Limited Company Buy to Let Variable Rate as a consequence of any one or more of the following matters occurring:  (i)   a change in the Lender’s costs in funding the Loan (this may include, for example, where there is an increase in the Bank of England base rate); (ii)   a change in the law, codes of practice or the way the Lender is regulated; or (iii)   a change beyond the Lender’s reasonable control in the costs to the Lender of providing the Loan or the  services and facilities available in connection with it 3.4   The Lender shall give notice to the Borrower (pursuant to General Condition 25) of any change in its Limited Company Buy to Let Variable Rate and will notify the Borrower of any change to the Borrower’s monthly  payment under General Condition 4.4 as a result of any change in its Limited Company Buy to Let Variable Rate.  4.   Repayment and Prepayment  4.1   The Borrower must repay the Loan and all other Loan Obligations in full on or before the Repayment Date.
5  4.2   The Borrower must make the monthly payments set out in the Facility Letter, as varied from time to time under General Condition 4.4, until the Loan is repaid in full. These payments will start in the month in which the Loan is advanced to the Borrower and will be due on the last business day of the month. 4.3   Monthly payments must be made by direct debit from a UK based bank account and in pounds sterling. 4.4   In certain circumstances, the Lender may vary the monthly payment amount. The Lender may do this if:  (i)   there is a change in the Interest Rate; (ii)   the full amount of the Loan is not made in accordance with the terms of the Facility Letter; (iii)   a change to the term of the Loan is agreed between the Borrower and the Lender in writing; (iv)   any part of the Loan is prepaid in accordance with these General Conditions; (v)   the change is needed to provide (where regulatory requirements permit this) for any monthly payments  which the Borrower has failed to pay to be rescheduled for payment over the rest of the term of the  Loan until the Repayment Date; or (vi)   the change is required by any change in applicable law or regulation The Lender will notify the Borrower not less than 10 Business Days in advance if the Borrower’s payment  amount is changing and when the first revised payment is due.  (ii)   The Borrower may on giving not less than 5 Business Days’ notice in writing to the Lender prepay all or  part of the Loan at any time. All prepayments must be made together with Interest accrued on the amounts prepaid and the other sums payable as a consequence of that prepayment in accordance with the Facility Document. 4.5   If all or any part of the Loan is prepaid or cancelled, the Borrower shall indemnify and pay to the Lender on demand an additional sum determined by the Lender as representing all costs, loss and liability to the Lender arising as a result of such prepayment or cancellation (including, without limitation, mid-interest period break costs and any breakage funding costs arising in relation to any fixed rate funding (including the cost of having to liquidate or re-deploy funds acquired or committed to make, fund or maintain the Loan or any part of it, or liquidating, cancelling or varying transactions entered into to match hedge or fund the Loan or any part  of it)), together with any administrative or other fee that may be payable as a result of that prepayment in  accordance with the Tariff of Charges. 4.6   Any prepayment of the Loan will be applied to reduce the amount of the Loan with effect from the last day of the calendar month in which the prepayment is made. 4.7   Any amount of the Loan that is repaid or prepaid cannot be reborrowed. 4.8   The Borrower is not entitled to cancel all or any part of the Loan. 4.9   If the Lender or a Receiver sell a Charged Property following enforcement action against the Borrower or any Security Provider, the Borrower must still pay the Lender any amount by which the sale proceeds fall short of the outstanding balance of the Loan. If the shortfall is not paid immediately, the Lender may continue to charge interest at the applicable Interest Rate until paid in full.  5.   Representation and Warranties  5.1   The Borrower and each Security Provider makes the representations and warranties set out below to the Lender on the date of the Facility Letter, on each date on which a Loan is made by the Lender to the Borrower and on the last day of each calendar month (in each case, by reference to the facts and  circumstances then prevailing on each such date): (i)   It is a limited liability company duly incorporated and validly existing under the laws of its jurisdiction  of incorporation and possesses the capacity to sue and be sued in its own name and has the power to own its assets and to carry on its business as it is being conducted.  (ii)   The entry into and performance by it of, and the transactions contemplated by, the Facility Documents  and the granting of the Transaction Security do not and will not conflict with: any law or regulation  applicable to it; its constitutional documents; or any agreement or instrument binding upon it or any of its assets or constitute a default or termination event (however described) under any such agreement or  instrument.
6  (iii)   It has the power to enter into each Facility Document to which it is a party and to exercise its rights  and perform its obligations under each such Facility Document, and has taken all necessary corporate and other action to authorise its entry into each Facility Document to which it is a party and to exercise its rights and perform its obligations under each such Facility Document.  (iv)   All Authorisations required to enable it lawfully to enter into, exercise its rights and comply with its  obligations in the Facility Documents to which it is a party have been obtained or effected and are in full force and effect.  (v)   Subject to registration (or due presentation for registration) of the Facility Documents at applicable  registries and to public policy general equitable principles and insolvency and other laws generally applicable to creditors rights, each Facility Document to which each Borrower or Security Provider is  a party constitutes, or will constitute when executed in accordance with its terms, that person’s legal,  valid and binding obligations enforceable in accordance with its terms.  (vi)   No Event of Default is continuing or is reasonably likely to result from the making of the Loan or the entry into; or the performance of, or any transaction contemplated by, any Facility Document. (vii)   Unless otherwise specified in the Facility Letter, the Borrower has not traded or carried on any business  or incurred any liabilities since its formation other than conducting the business of acquiring, managing and owning a Charged Property and liabilities arising directly from that business.  (viii)   Except as disclosed to the Lender in any report or certificate on title prepared for its benefit prior to the  drawdown of the Loan, no Security exists over the assets of the Borrower or any Security Provider, and the Borrower and each Security Provider is the legal and beneficial owner of, and has a good and valid title to, each of its assets which are expressed to be the subject of any Transaction Security.  (ix)   The Borrower and each Security Provider has in all material respects performed and complied with all Environmental Law relating to a Charged Property (including MEES). (x)   All information supplied by or on behalf of the Borrower and each Security Provider to the Lender in  connection with the Facility Documents, a Charged Property, each valuation, each certificate or report on title and the transactions contemplated by them is complete and accurate, and it has not knowingly withheld any information which if disclosed might reasonably be expected to adversely affect the decision of the Lender considering whether or not to provide finance to the Borrower.  (xi)   No litigation, arbitration or administrative proceeding or investigation of, or before, any court, arbitral  body or agency which, if adversely determined, are reasonably likely to have a Material Adverse Effect  have (to the best of its knowledge and belief (having made due and careful enquiry)) been started or  threatened against it.  (xii)   No judgement or order of a court, arbitral body or agency which is reasonably likely to have a Material Adverse Effect has (to the best of its knowledge and belief (having made due and careful enquiry)) been  made against it.  (xiii)   No claim proceeding or investigation in respect of Environmental Law has been commenced or (to the best of its knowledge and belief) is threatened against it. (xiv)   The financial statements of the Borrower and any Security Provider most recently delivered to the  Lender pursuant to the Facility Documents have been prepared in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles consistently applied.  6.   Undertakings  6.1   The Borrower and each Security Provider undertake and covenant as follows:  (i)   It will obtain, comply with and do all that is necessary to maintain in full force and effect any  Authorisation required under any applicable law or regulation to enable it to perform its obligations under the Facility Documents and to ensure the legality, validity, enforceability or admissibility in  evidence of any Facility Document; in connection with the management, use and occupation of any Charged Property; and to own its assets and carry on its business as it is being conducted. (ii)   It will not, without the prior written consent of the Lender, either in a single transaction or in a series of  transactions whether related or not and whether voluntarily or involuntarily, sell or transfer a Charged Property.
7  (iii)   It will comply with all covenants, agreements, stipulations and obligations now or at any time affecting  or binding any Charged Property insofar as the same are subsisting and are capable of being enforced, and it will duly and diligently enforce all covenants, agreements, stipulations and obligations benefiting  a Charged Property and will not waive, release (or vary or agree to do so) the obligations of any other  party thereto.  (iv)   It will keep each Charged Property in good and substantial repair and condition and, as appropriate,  good working order as to enable them to be let in accordance with all applicable laws and regulations and promptly after being required to do so by the Lender make good any want of repair of a Charged Property.  (v)   Where a Charged Property is subject to a Lease, it will diligently enforce the terms of the Lease against  the lessee.  (vi)   It will carry out any energy efficiency improvements necessary, or take any other steps necessary, to  ensure that at all times each part of a Charged Property which is designed to be let can be let or can continue to be let without breaching any applicable laws or regulations in respect of minimum levels of energy efficiency for properties.  (vii)   Where it derives its estate or interest in a Charged Property under a Lease it will: (a)   observe and perform all covenants, stipulations and obligations on the lessee under the Lease (b)   diligently enforce all covenants on the part of the lessor under the Lease (c)   not waive, release or vary any obligation under the Lease or exercise any option or power to break,  determine or extend the Lease  (d)   not agree to any change in the rent payable under the Lease without the prior written consent of  the Lender and  (e)   not do or permit anything whereby the Lease may be forfeited and (f)   promptly notify the Lender of any matter or event under or by reason of which the Lease has or  may become subject to determination or the exercise of any right of re-entry or forfeiture and, if so requested by the Lender, the Security Provider will apply for relief against forfeiture in accordance with the instructions of the Lender  (viii)   It will pay when due all (if applicable) future rents, ground rents, rates, taxes, assessments and outgoings  payable in respect of a Charged Property whether by the owner or the occupier.  (ix)   It will not, without the prior written consent of the Lender, carry out any structural alterations, additions,  demolition, reconstruction or rebuilding on or of a Charged Property or make any material change in use of a Charged Property, other than minor works that do not adversely affect the structural integrity of any building or the value of a Charged Property.  (x)   It will comply in all respects with all planning laws, permissions, agreements and conditions to which a  Charged Property may be subject.  (xi)   It will ensure that any unfinished building or works on a Charged Property are completed without delay  and are carried out to the required standard.  (xii)   It will not do or permit to be done anything which may in any way adversely affect the value of a  Charged Property or jeopardise, depreciate or otherwise prejudice any rights or assets secured in favour of the Lender.  (xiii)   If requested by the Lender, it will procure that any professional advisers appointed in connection with  construction work on a Charged Property enter into a Professional Warranty with the Lender covering their respective professional obligations to the Lender in a form satisfactory to the Lender.  (xiv)   It will obtain and maintain any permits, registrations, licences, exemptions, consents or other approvals  required for its business, or in respect of a Charged Property land title, any notification or report on assessment required under any Environmental Law.  (xv)   If requested by the Lender it will provide the Lender with an environmental audit report carried out by  a specialist surveyor or consultant and will implement any steps recommended to be implemented in any such report as soon as reasonably practicable.
8  (xvi)   Subject to the terms of any Lease, it will allow the Lender, the Lender’s employees or agents, after  giving reasonable notice, to enter a Charged Property to examine its state and condition or for any other purpose permitted by or connected with any Facility Document, including the carrying out of a valuation of a Charged Property and carry out or complete any work which is needed to put right any failure by the Borrower to comply with these General Conditions without thereby becoming a mortgagee in possession.  (xvii)   If there is any breach of its obligations under a Facility Document, the Lender may carry out such works,  or take such other action or steps as the Lender considers appropriate to remedy the breach.  (xviii)   If any part or interest in a Charged Property is compulsory purchased or is expropriated any payment  paid to it will be applied in or towards repayment of the Loan Obligation, unless the Lender agrees otherwise in writing. 6.2   The Borrower and each Security Provider further undertakes and covenants as follows.  (i)   It will not create or permit to subsist any Security on any Charged Property or any other asset over  which it has granted Security to the Lender.  (ii)   It will not enter into any amalgamation, demerger, merger or corporate restructure. (iii)   It shall not declare or pay any dividends or interest on unpaid dividends or any other distribution to  any of its members, directors, partners, beneficiaries or affiliates or make any other payments in relation to any loan or indebtedness owed by it to any such person at any time while an Event of Default is continuing.  (iv)   It will notify the Lender in writing should any person acquire, in aggregate, 30 per cent or more of its  issued share capital.  (v)   If an Event of Default is continuing, it will not, without the prior written consent of the Lender: (a)   redeem or purchase its own shares or (b)   pay or repay any abnormal amount to its directors (or any person who has, since the date of the Facility Letter, been a director of the Borrower or that Security Provider)  6.3  (i)   The Security Provider consents to an application being made to the Chief Land Registrar for registration  on the register of title of all such present and future registered freehold, leasehold or commonhold  property (and any unregistered properties subject to compulsory first registration). (ii)   The Security Provider confirms that so far as any of a Charged Property is unregistered, such land is not  affected by any disclosable overriding interests within the meaning of the Land Registration Act 2002 or the Land Registration Rules 2003.  (iii)   Where applicable, the Lender and the Security Provider consent to an application being made to the  Chief Land Registrar to enter a note of such obligation on the register of title to all present and future registered property of the Security Provider comprised within a Charged Property (and any unregistered  properties subject to compulsory first registration at the date of the Security Document).  6.4   Each Security Provider will immediately upon the execution of the relevant Security Document (or upon  coming into the possession of a Security Provider at any time) deposit with the Lender all deeds, certificates  and other documents constituting or evidencing title to any asset which is subject to fixed Security in favour of the Lender. 6.5   Each Security Provider will, promptly on the request of the Lender from time to time give notice of  assignment or charge (in such form as the Lender may require) in respect of any asset which is the subject of  an assignment or charge pursuant to a Facility Document and will use all reasonable endeavours to procure that the recipient of that notice acknowledges receipt in a form satisfactory to the Lender. 6.6   Each Security Provider and the Borrower will do all acts and execute all documents (including mortgages,  charges, transfers, assurances, assignments notices and instructions) as the Lender may from time to time  require:  (i)   to secure the Loan Obligations or perfect or preserve the Security created or intended to be created by any Facility Document, and/or
9  (ii)   for the exercise of the rights, powers and remedies of the Lender or a Receiver provided by or pursuant to any Facility Document or by law, and/or (iii)   to facilitate the realisation of a Charged Property or any asset which is the subject of Security in favour  of the Lender  7.   Use and Occupation of a Charged Property  7.1   The Borrower and each Security Provider must use a Charged Property only for letting for residential purposes as a private dwelling. 7.2   The Borrower and each Security Provider must not occupy a Charged Property itself and must not agree to grant a tenancy of any Charged Property to any of the following:  (i)   its family members (including, without limitation, its spouse, civil partner, parents, grandparents, siblings, children and grandchildren); (ii)   tenants in receipt of housing benefit; (iii)   local authority tenants; and (iv)   people who could claim diplomatic immunity  7.3   The Borrower and each Security Provider must ensure that any tenancy agreement for a Charged Property created with a non-corporate tenant complies with the following:  (i)   any tenancy of a Charged Property must in all respects comply with the Housing Act 1996 as an assured shorthold tenancy; Order of Payments and Application of Proceeds  17.1   If the Lender receives a payment that is insufficient to discharge all the amounts then due and payable by the Borrower or any Security Provider under the Facility Documents, the Lender shall apply that payment towards the obligations of the Borrower and the Security Providers under the Facility Documents in such order as the Lender requires. 17.2   All moneys received or recovered by the Lender or any Receiver pursuant to any Security Document or the powers conferred by it shall (subject to the claims of any person having prior rights thereto by way of a  variation of the provisions of the Law of Property Act 1925) be applied towards the following items in the  following order:  (i)   first, in the payment of all costs, charges and expenses of and incidental to the Receiver’s appointment  and his remuneration  (ii)   second in the payment or discharge of any liabilities incurred by a Receiver on the exercise of any  powers of the Receiver  (iii)   third, in providing for the matters (other than the remuneration of the Receiver) specified in the first three paragraphs of Section 109(8) of the Law of Property Act 1925 in or towards any payment of any  debts or claims which are by statute payable in preference to the Lender but only to the extent to which such debts or claims shall have such preference and  (iv)   fourth, in or towards the satisfaction of the Loan Obligations in such order as the Lender shall direct and (v)   thereafter any such surplus being paid to the person then entitled to such surplus  The above shall override any appropriation made by the Borrower or a Security Provider.  18.   Security Power of Attorney  18.1   Each Security Provider by way of security, irrevocably and severally agrees to appoint the Lender, each Receiver and any of their delegates or sub-delegates to be its attorney to take any action which the Security Provider is obliged to take under the Facility Documents.
18  18.2   Each Security Provider agrees to ratify and confirm all things done and all documents executed by any attorney in the exercise or purported exercise of all and any of his powers.  19.   Waiver of Defences  19.1   The obligations of the Borrower and each Security Provider under each Facility Document shall not be affected by any act, omission, matter or thing which, but for this General Condition 19, would reduce, increase or prejudice any of its obligations under any facility Document, including:  (i)   any time waiver or consent granted to, or composition with, the Borrower, a Security Provider or  other person  (ii)   the release of the Borrower, a Security Provider or any other person under the terms of any composition  or arrangement with any creditor of the Borrower or a Security Provider  (iii)   the taking, variation, compromise, exchange, renewal or release of or refusal or neglect to perfect, take  up or enforce any rights against or security over assets of the Borrower, a Security Provider or any other person or non-presentation or non-observance of any formality or other requirement in respect of any instrument or any failure to realise the full value of any security  (iv)   any incapacity or lack of power, authority or legal personality of or dissolution or change in the  members or status of the Borrower, a Security Provider or any other person  (v)   any amendment (however fundamental) or replacement of any Facility Document or any other  document or security  (vi)   any unenforceability, illegality or invalidity of any obligation of any person under any Facility Document  or any other document or security, or  (vii)   any insolvency or similar proceedings  20.   No Liability  None of the Lender, its nominee(s) or any Receiver will be liable by reason of taking action permitted by any  Facility Document or any neglect or default in connection with any asset which is secured in favour of the Lender or taking possession of or realising all or any part of any asset which is secured in favour of the Lender except in the case of gross negligence or wilful default upon its part.  21.   Consolidation and Set off  21.1   Each Security Document and all other Security shall be security not only for the moneys primarily provided for it but also for all moneys which may be or become owning by the Borrower or a Security Provider to the  Lender on any account and (save at the discretion of the Lender) no Charged Property held by the Lender as  Security shall be released until the Loan Obligations have been paid in full . 22.2   The Borrower and each Security Provider authorises the Lender to apply any credit balance to which the Borrower or that Security Provider is entitled on any account of the Borrower or a Security Provider with the Lender in satisfaction of any sum due and payable from the Borrower or that Security Provider to the Lender pursuant to the Facility Documents. 22.3   The Lender may set off any matured obligation due from the Borrower under the Facility Documents against any matured obligation owed by the Lender to the Borrower, regardless of the place of payment, booking branch or currency of either obligation. 22.4   All payments to be made to the Lender under the Facility Documents shall be calculated and made without  (and free and clear of any deduction for) set-off or counterclaim.  22.   Payments  22.1   All payments by the Borrower to the Lender must be made to such account as the Lender may notify to the Borrower from time to time. Time of payment by the Borrower is of the essence of the Facility Documents. Payments are sent at the risk of the Borrower and the Lender is not responsible for loss of or delay to payments sent by or to the Borrower.
19  22.2   Any payment under the Facility Documents which is due to be made on a day that is not a Business Day shall  be made on the next Business Day in the same calendar month (if there is one) or the preceding Business Day (if there is not).  22.3   Any Interest, Default Interest, commission or fee accruing under a Facility Document will accrue from day to day and on the basis of a year of 365 days.  23.   Indemnities, Costs and Expenses  23.1   The Borrower will on demand indemnify the Lender against any cost, loss or liability (including any breakage  costs and loss or margin) incurred by the Lender as a result of: (i)   the occurrence of any Event of Default or investigating any event which it reasonably believes is an  Event of Default or is likely to give rise to an Event of Default  (ii)   any failure by the Borrower or a Security Provider to pay any amount due under the Facility Document  on its due date  (iii)   the Loan not being made on the date requested by the Borrower by reason or the operation of any one  or more of the provisions of the Facility Documents  (iv)   any part of the Loan not being prepaid in accordance with any notice of prepayment given by the  Borrower  (v)   acting on or relying on any notice, request or instruction which it reasonably believes to be genuine,  correct and appropriately authorised or  (vi)   any claim proceedings or investigation under any Environmental Law in connection with the Borrower,  any Security Provider or a Charged Property  Such cost, loss or liability may include: (i) without limitation the cost of having to liquidate or re-deploy  funds acquired or committed to make, fund or maintain the Loan or any part of it or liquidating or varying  transactions entered into an order to match hedge or fund the Loan or any part of it; (ii) the cost of utilising management and administration time and other resources of the Lender and/or the Lender appointing any  agent to act on its behalf therewith. 23.2   The Borrower will, on demand, pay to the Lender the amount of all costs and expenses (including legal and  valuation fees and expenses, documentation fees, VAT and any other out of pocket expenses) incurred by the  Lender in connection with:  (i)   the preparation, execution and implementation of the Facility Letter, each other Facility Document and  any other document referred to in a Facility Document  (ii)   an amendment, waiver or consent to any term of any Facility Document requested by the Borrower or a  Security Provider, or  (iii)   any valuation, survey or environmental report obtained by the Lender which discloses an Event of  Default  23.3   The Borrower will, on demand, pay to the Lender the amount of all costs and expenses (including legal fees)  incurred by the Lender in connection with the enforcement of, or the preservation of any rights under, any Facility Document. 23.4   The Borrower agrees that the Lender may deduct from the drawdown of the Loan an amount equal to all fees, costs and expenses then due to the Lender pursuant to any Facility Document. 23.5   The Borrower will on demand indemnify the Lender for any Increased Cost it incurs and will promptly pay the amount that the Lender certifies as payable and the Lender will also disclose in reasonable detail the basis  of its calculation (but not any matter that it considers to be confidential).  24.   Transfers and Assignments  24.1   The Lender may at any time, in its absolute discretion, with or without notice to the Borrower or any Security Provider, transfer, novate, assign, charge or otherwise dispose of the benefit of the Facility Documents or any  Facility Document (including without limitation the Loan Obligations, any Security and all the Lender’s rights and remedies in relation to the Facility Documents) to any person (whether or not associated with the Lender  and the Borrower and each Security Provider consents to any such transfer, novation, assignment, charge or
20  disposal and agrees that it shall be bound to such person (and any successor in title, transferee or assign of  such person) in the manner and to the same extent as it is bound to the Lender.  24.2   The Borrower may not and no Security Provider may assign or transfer any of its rights or obligations under the Facility Letter or any Facility Document.  25.   Notices  25.1   Subject to General Condition 26 below, any notice, demand or other communication to be made in relation to a Facility Document will be given in writing and will be deemed to be given if in writing and delivered to:  (a)   the Borrower or Security Provider personally or sent by prepaid post to its registered office or present or last known business or private address (as appropriate) or (b)   to the Lender personally or sent by prepaid post to its address set out in the Facility Letter and marked  for the attention of the Head of Commercial Lending 25.2   Any notice or other communication received on a non-Business Day or after business hours in the place of receipt will only be deemed to be given on the next Business Day. 25.3   The address of each person for all notices, demands and other communications as are set out in the Facility Letter or if no such details are set out in the Facility Letter as notified by the person to the Lender by not less  than 5 Business Days’ notice.  26.   Electronic Communication  26.1   Any communication to be made between any two parties in relation to a Facility Document may be made by electronic mail or other electronic means (including, without limitation, by way of posting to a secure  website) if the relevant parties: (i)   notify each other in writing of their electronic mail address and/or any other information required to enable the transmission of information by that means; (ii)   notify each other of any change to their address or any other such information supplied by them not less than five Business Days’ notice  26.2   Any such electronic communication as specified in General Condition 26.1 above made between the relevant  Parties will be effective only when actually received (or made available) in readable form and in the case of  any electronic communication made by any person to the Lender only if it is addressed in such a manner as the Lender shall specify for this purpose. 26.3   Any electronic communication which becomes effective, in accordance with General Condition 26.2 above,  after 5:00pm (GMT) shall be deemed only to become effective on the following Business Day.  27.   Disclosure  27.1   The Borrower and each Security Provider agree (to the extent permitted by law and regulation) that the  Lender may from time to time disclose to:  (i)   any regulatory authority (ii)   any affiliate of the Lender (iii)   any person appointed to administer the Loan (iv)   any credit reference or rating agency (v)   any person with whom it is proposing to enter, or has entered into, any kind of assignment, transfer, securitisation, participation or other disposal in relation to this Loan and such person’s Affiliates (vi)   any legal and other professional advisers to any person listed in this General Condition or (vii)   any person to whom disclosure is required by law  a copy of any Facility Document and any information which the Lender has acquired or acquires from time to time from the Borrower any Security Provider or any other third party under or in connection with this Loan.
21  27.2   The Lender and any person associated with the Lender and/or any company approved by the Lender may  use any information provided by the Borrower or the Security Provider to administer the facilities made available to the Borrower to develop further goods and services for statistical and business analysis and for creating and maintaining a customer profile.  27.3   The Lender and any company associated with the Lender and/or any company approved by the Lender  may use any information provided by the Borrower or any Security Provider (or any other person to advise  the Borrower or any Security Provider) by post, telephone, or other electronic media about other products  and services which may be of interest to the Borrower or any Security Provider unless the Borrower or any Security Provider notifies the Lender in writing that it does not wish to be so advised.  28.   Partial Invalidity  If at any time any clause, paragraph or provision of any Facility Document is or becomes invalid, illegal or unenforceable in any respect under any law of any jurisdiction neither the validity, legality or enforceability of the remaining clauses, nor the legality, validity or enforceability of such provision under the law of any other jurisdiction will in any way be affected or impaired.  29.   Waivers and Amendments  The Lender may from time to time waive any requirement of any Facility Document. No amendment or waiver of a Facility Document will be valid unless made to or agreed in writing by the Lender and such agreement communicated to the Borrower.  30.   Complaints  30.1   The Lender hopes to resolve any issues as soon as made aware about them. However, if the Borrower feels this has not been achieved, the Lender has clear and simple procedures in place to make sure it handles issues and complaints fairly, sensitively and in line with the requirements of the Financial Conduct Authority. 30.2   The Lender aims to investigate every complaint about its services. 30.3   The Lender aims to keep the Borrower updated whilst investigating a complaint until it is able to provide the Borrower with a formal resolution letter.  30.4   Despite this not being a product regulated by the Financial Ombudsman Service (FOS), in exceptional circumstances, particularly where the Borrower’s complaint is complex, it may take over eight weeks to  resolve matters for the Borrower. At this point, the Lender will write to the Borrower to acknowledge the Borrower may wish to contact the FOS to review the complaint. The Borrower can contact the FOS either via  their website at http://www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk/ or via post at The Financial Ombudsman Service,  Exchange Tower, London, E14 9SR.  30.5   For a full outline of the Lender’s complaints procedures and how to make a complaint, please   go to the West Bromwich website at: www.westbrom.co.uk/customer-support/complaints 31.   Data Protection  The Lender confirms that all personal data of the Borrower, any Guarantor and any Security Provider will  be processed in accordance with its “customer privacy notice”. For a full outline of the Lender’s “customer privacy notice”, please   go to the West Bromwich website at: www.westbrom.co.uk/subs-privacy-notice 32.   Governing Law  Each Facility Document and any non-contractual obligations arising out of or in connection with it are governed by English Law.
22  33.   Jurisdiction  33.1   The courts of England have exclusive jurisdiction to settle any dispute arising out of or in connection with the Facility Documents including any dispute regarding the existence, validity or termination of any Facility Documents or any non-contractual obligation arising out of or in connection with any Facility Document. 33.2   The Borrower and each Security Provider agree that the courts of England are the most appropriate and convenient courts to settle disputes and will not argue to the contrary. 33.3   For the benefit of the Lender only, the Lender shall not be prevented from taking proceedings relating to a dispute in any other court with jurisdiction and, to the extent allowed by law, the Lender may take concurrent proceedings in any number of jurisdictions.  34.   Counterparts  Each Facility Document may be executed in any number of counterparts and this has the effect as if signatures on the counterparts were on a single copy of the relevant document.  35.   Miscellaneous  35.1   The Lender’s determination of the Interest, Default Interest or the amount of any other payment to be made  by the Borrower or a Security Provider under the Facility Documents shall, in the absence of manifest error, be conclusive and binding. 35.2   All amounts expressed to be payable under a Facility Document to the Lender are deemed to be exclusive of VAT. If VAT is chargeable on any supply made by the Lender to any person in connection with a Facility Document, that person will pay to the Lender (in addition to and at the same time as paying the relevant  amount) an amount equal to the amount of VAT.
